8 positive cases were found - indicates a decrease in cases. People related to Markaz,who returned on 25, 26 & 27 March,are also being tested today: Telangana Health Minpic.twitter.com/Dehwl87xIr|last=ANI|date=2020-04-09|website=@ANI|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Uttar Pradesh|Uttar Pradesh]]\n|845\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ANINewsUP/status/1252244640079556609/photo/2|title=84 More #COVID19 cases reported in Uttar Pradesh today. Total number of cases in the state is at 1184, including 1026 active cases, 140 discharged, and 18 deaths: State Health Departmentpic.twitter.com/LtIbpWYmW9|last=UP|first=ANI|date=2020-04-20|website=@ANINewsUP|language=en|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Uttarakhand]]\n|24\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref name=\":42\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/india/coronavirus-uttarakhand-dgp-warns-tablighi-members-dgp-6348933/|title=Uttarakhand DGP warns Tablighi members: 'Report to authorities by April 6 or face murder bid charge if any case reported'|date=2020-04-06|website=The Indian Express|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jagran.com/uttarakhand/dehradun-city-coronavirus-outbreak-for-more-patients-found-coronavirus-positive-in-uttarakhand-20175471.html|title=coronavirus: \u0909\u0924\u094d\u0924\u0930\u093e\u0916\u0902\u0921 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0924\u0940\u0928 \u091c\u092e\u093e\u0924\u093f\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0938\u092e\u0947\u0924 \u091a\u093e\u0930 \u0915\u094b\u0930\u094b\u0928\u093e \u092a\u0949\u091c\u093f\u091f\u093f\u0935, 35 \u092a\u0939\u0941\u0902\u091a\u0940 \u0938\u0902\u0916\u094d\u092f\u093e|website=Dainik Jagran|language=hi|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n|-\n!Total\n!3,776*\n!27*\n!\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" |''<small>*These numbers are not complete as some States do not report hotspot sources for cases</small>''\n|}\n\n==== March ====\n\n* On March 18, Eight Indonesians of Tablighi Jamaat were tested positive in [[Karimnagar]] in Telangana.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-in-india-high-alert-in-telangana-after-8-indonesians-test-positive-for-covid-19-1657355-2020-03-19|title=Coronavirus in India: High alert in Telangana after 8 Indonesians test positive for Covid-19|last=HyderabadMarch 19|first=Indo-Asian News Service|last2=March 19|first2=2020UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04|last3=Ist|first3=2020 12:45}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/south/covid-19-telanganas-karimnagar-reports-eight-covid-19-positive-cases-city-under-lockdown-815287.html|title=COVID-19: Telangana's Karimnagar reports eight COVID-19 positive cases; city under lockdown|date=2020-03-19|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> They had arrived from Hazrat Nizammudin, Delhi on March 14.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://telanganatoday.com/karimnagar-six-secondary-contacts-of-indonesian-preacher-shifted-to-isolation-ward|title=Karimnagar: Six secondary contacts of Indonesian preacher shifted to isolation ward|last=AuthorTelanganaToday|website=Telangana Today|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> Security agencies had traced the link of these cases to Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/markaz-leadership-resisted-then-nsa-ajit-doval-dropped-by-at-2-am/story-RhL243HMbRgTGBbriNIVzL.html|title=Markaz leadership resisted, then NSA Ajit Doval dropped by at 2 am|date=2020-04-01|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n* On March 21, two Thai Nationals in Erode, Tamil Nadu were reported as positive case number 5 and 6. They had attended this congregation in Delhi in early March.<ref>{{Cite news|last=M|first=Serena Josephine|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/25-of-67-patients-directly-or-indirectly-linked-to-thai-nationals/article31212197.ece|title=25 of 67 patients directly or indirectly linked to Thai nationals|date=2020-03-30|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-04|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/south/tamil-nadu-reports-17-fresh-coronavirus-cases-tally-now-67-819262.html|title=Tamil Nadu reports 17 fresh coronavirus cases; tally now 67|date=2020-03-30|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n*On March 26, Jammu and Kashmir reported first death to the pandemic, a 65 year old who had attended this congregation.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/tracking-covid-19-super-spreader-from-j-k-to-tablighi-event-in-delhi-and-back-via-up/articleshow/74911674.cms?from=mdr|title=Tracking COVID-19 'super spreader': From J-K to Tablighi event in Delhi and back via UP|date=2020-03-31|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> At that time, more than 40 of 48 cases in the region was tracked back to this patient.<ref name=\":7\" />\n* On March 31, 57 new cases were reported in Tamil Nadu. 80 out of total 124 cases in the state are linked to Tablighi Jamaat cluster.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/tamil-nadu-reports-57-new-covid-19-cases-in-one-day-79-attended-tablighi-jamaat-state-tally-at-124-1661904-2020-03-31|title=Tamil Nadu reports 57 new Covid-19 cases in one day, 79% attended Tablighi Jamaat. State tally at 124|last=ChennaiMarch 31|first=Shalini Lobo|last2=March 31|first2=2020UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04|last3=Ist|first3=2020 21:56}}</ref>\n\n==== April ====\n\n* First positive case from [[Dharavi]] in [[Mumbai]] who eventually died on April 1, has hosted 10 Tablighi Jamaat members between March 22 and March 25.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/coronavirus-in-mumbai-dharavi-man-covid-19-patient-hosted-10-tablighi-jamaat-members-nizamuddin-604366|title=Coronavirus in Mumbai: Dharavi man who died due to COVID-19 hosted 10 Tablighi Jamaa