s-total-goes-up-to-485/article31258036.ece|title=Coronavirus {{!}} TN reports 74 new cases; total goes up to 485|date=2020-04-04|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-04|others=PTI|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> In Assam, 25 out of 26 cases reported until this date had taken part in this event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/assam-coronavirus-infected-man-met-111-search-for-silent-carrier-on-2206264|title=Assam Coronavirus-Infected Man Met 111, Search For \"Silent Carrier\" On|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n*On April 5, Tamil Nadu positive cases reached 571 in which 522 are related to this hotspot.<ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://stopcorona.tn.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Media-Bulletin-05-04-20-COVID-19-6-PM.pdf|title=TamilNadu Media Bulletin 05.04.2020 6PM|last=|first=|date=|website=tn.gov.in|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200405215542/https://stopcorona.tn.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Media-Bulletin-05-04-20-COVID-19-6-PM.pdf|archive-date=2020-04-05|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> In Uttar Pradesh, out of 139 out of 283 cases reported until this date has linkage to this cluster and in Delhi it is 320 out of 503 total cases.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/lucknow-city-coronavirus-death-in-up-old-aged-man-from-varanasi-coronavirus-positive-died-third-from-up-20166377.html|title=CoronaVirus death in UP : \u0909\u0924\u094d\u0924\u0930 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0926\u0947\u0936 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0915\u094b\u0930\u094b\u0928\u093e \u0935\u093e\u092f\u0930\u0938 \u0938\u0947 \u0924\u0940\u0938\u0930\u0940 \u092e\u094c\u0924, \u0905\u092c \u0924\u0915 284 \u092a\u0949\u091c\u093f\u091f\u093f\u0935|website=Dainik Jagran|language=hi|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/delhi-new-covid19-cases-coronavirus-lockdown-604836|title=58 new COVID-19 cases reported in Delhi, tally rises to 503|last=Pathak|first=Analiza|date=2020-04-05|website=www.indiatvnews.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n*On 9 April, 97 new cases, all linked to the Tablighi Jamaat event, were reported in Delhi, bringing the total number linked to this cluster to 430 in Delhi, out Of 669 for all cases.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/coronavirus-tablighi-jamaat-delhi-93-new-covid-19-cases-in-delhi-linked-to-mosque-event-426-of-669-o-2208733 |title=93 New COVID-19 Cases In Delhi Linked To Mosque Event, 426 Of 669 Overall |work=NDTV |date=9 April 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== Reconciliation efforts ==\nIn April 2020 the Tamil Nadu government proposed to start trials for convalescent plasma therapy to treat COVID-19 patients as it was believed that plasma from recovered COVID-19 patients will have antibodies to the virus which will help treat others who have contracted Covid19. In line with this decision, a group of Tamil Nadu Tablighi Jamaat members who attended the Delhi events announced their decision to donate their plasma to help other patients recover from COVID-19. Local Muslim religious leaders also encouraged these recovered COVID-19 patients, especially youngsters, to donate their plasma once the government makes a formal announcement in this regard.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sivapriyan |first1=ETB |title=TN Tablighi attendees ready to donate plasma for COVID-19 treatment |url=https://www.deccanherald.com/amp/national/tn-tablighi-attendees-ready-to-donate-plasma-for-covid-19-treatment-828144.html?fbclid=IwAR1Dp-CKVePU-L8Ml_D8EcGYkTc0J94UD_SuRtRunbf-2ALpqP0qYeuvgxA |website=[[Deccan Herald]] |publisher=Deccan Herald |accessdate=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Related casualties==\nIn [[Prayagraj]] in [[Uttar Pradesh]], a man was shot dead for making remarks against Tablighi Jamaat.\n<ref>\n[https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/up-man-shot-dead-at-tea-shop-for-blaming-tablighi-jamaat-for-coronavirus-spread-1663552-2020-04-05 UP man shot dead at tea shop for blaming Tablighi Jamaat for coronavirus spread], India Today, 5 April 2020.\n</ref>\n\nIn Una district in [[Himachal Pradesh]], a man hanged himself due to taunts from fellow villagers for having come in contact with Tablighi Jamaat missionaries.<ref>\n[https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/himachal/himachal-man-commits-suicide-after-insults-over-coronavirus-spread-post-tablighi-congregation-65978 Taunted over coronavirus spread after Tablighi meet, Himachal man commits suicide], The Tribune (Chandigarh), 5 April 2020.\n</ref>\n\nSeveral truckers belonging to the Muslim community were allegedly beaten up in [[Arunachal Pradesh]] following which they fled to neighbouring [[Assam]], leaving their vehicles behind on 5 April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/muslim-truckers-beaten-up-in-arunachal-concern-over-supplies-of-essential-items-2565619.html |title=Muslim Truckers 'Beaten Up' in Arunachal, Concern Over Supplies of Essential Items |date=5 April 2020 |website=CNN-News18 |access-date=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nA Delhi Muslim man was beaten up by a mob accusing him of spreading coronavirus because he had participated in a religious gathering.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kolkata |first1=Hannah Ellis-Petersen Shaikh Azizur Rahman in |title=Coronavirus conspiracy theories targeting Muslims spread in India |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/13/coronavirus-conspiracy-theories-targeting-muslims-spread-in-india |accessdate=22 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Pakistan]]\n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Tablighi Jamaat}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in India]]\n[[Category:Tablighi Jamaat]]\n[[Category:2020s in Delhi]]\n", "name_user": "Shanze1", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up"